s: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\">Not everything goes the way we want it to - the world or people around us sometimes just spin out of control. Just consider the Covid pandemic for starters. Or how about that mad neighbour you have living next-door to you? Or when work seems to be going down the toilet when the competition keep outsmarting you? So how do you handle everything life throws your way when you&#39;d really prefer to tell everyone to get stuffed?</p>', '2024-06-13 22:15:04', '2024-06-13 22:15:04');
INSERT INTO `Books` VALUES (7, 'The Power Of Regret: How Looking Backward Moves Us Forward', 9, 5, 6, 8, 1, 2022, NULL, 189000, 700, 0, 230, 'Bìa mềm', '14.5 x 20.5', '1718291941391-208834298.jpg', '<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow: hidden; max-height: 600px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\" id=\"isPasted\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block !important; line-height: 25px;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Power Of Regret: How Looking Backward Moves Us Forward</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">From Daniel H. Pink, the #1 New York Times-bestselling author of When and Drive, a new book about the transforming power of our most misunderstood yet potentially most valuable emotion: regret.</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">Everybody has regrets, Daniel H. Pink explains in The Power of Regret. They&rsquo;re a universal and healthy part of being human. And understanding how regret works can help us make smarter decisions, perform better at work and school, and bring greater meaning to our lives.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">Drawing on research in social psychology, neuroscience, and biology, Pink debunks the myth of the &ldquo;no regrets&rdquo; philosophy of life. And using the largest sampling of American attitudes about regret ever conducted as well as his own World Regret Survey&mdash;which has collected regrets from more than 15,000 people in 105 countries&mdash;he lays out the four core regrets that each of us has. These deep regrets offer compelling insights into how we live and how we can find a better path forward.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">As he did in his bestsellers Drive, When, and A Whole New Mind, Pink lays out a dynamic new way of thinking about regret and frames his ideas in ways that are clear, accessible, and pragmatic. Packed with true stories of people&#39;s regrets as well as practical takeaways for reimagining regret as a positive force, The Power of Regret shows how we can live richer, more engaged lives.</p></div></div></div><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; overflow-y: hidden;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: -600px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block !important; line-height: 25px;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px;\"><br></div></div></div></div>', '2024-06-13 22:19:19', '2024-06-13 22:19:19');
INSERT INTO `Books` VALUES (8, 'The Power Of Habit', 7, 3, 5, 7, 1, 2022, NULL, 600000, 560, 0, 569, 'Bìa cứng', '14.5 x 20.5', '1718292292468-28069942.jpg', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\" id=\"isPasted\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Why do we do develop habits? And how can we change them?</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">We can always change. In&nbsp;</span><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-style: italic;\">The Power of Habit,&nbsp;</em><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">award-winning&nbsp;</span><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-style: italic;\">New York Times</em><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">&nbsp;business reporter Charles Duhigg translates cutting-edge behavioural science into practical self-improvement action, distilling advanced neuroscience into fascinating narratives of transformation.</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">Why can some people and companies change overnight, and some stay stuck in their old ruts? The answer lies deep in the human brain, and&nbsp;</span><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-style: italic;\">The Power of Habits&nbsp;</em><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">reveals the secret pressure points that can change a life. From Olympic swimmer Michael Phelps to Martin Luther King Jr., from the CEO of Starbucks to the locker rooms of the NFL, Duhigg explores the incredible results of&nbsp;</span><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-style: italic;\">keystone habits</em><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em;\">, and how they can make all the difference between billions and millions, failure and success &ndash; or even life and death</span></p>', '2024-06-13 22:25:48', '2024-06-13 22:25:48');
INSERT INTO `Books` VALUES (9, 'The Culture Code', 7, 3, 1, 6, 6, 2023, NULL, 670000, 800, 0, 500, 'Bìa mềm', '14.5 x 20.5', '1718292475739-750850553.jpg', '<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; overflow: hidden; max-height: 600px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\" id=\"isPasted\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block !important; line-height: 25px;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Culture Code</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\">NEW YORK TIMES BESTSELLER &bull; The&nbsp;author of The Talent Code&nbsp;unlocks the secrets of highly successful groups and provides tomorrow&rsquo;s leaders with the tools to build a cohesive, motivated culture.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\">Where does great culture come from? How do you build and sustain it in your group, or strengthen a culture that needs fixing?</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\">In The Culture Code, Daniel Coyle goes inside some of the world&rsquo;s most successful organizations&mdash;including the U.S. Navy&rsquo;s SEAL Team Six, IDEO, and the San Antonio Spurs&mdash;and reveals what makes them tick. He demystifies the culture-building process by identifying three key skills that generate cohesion and cooperation, and explains how diverse groups learn to function with a single mind. Drawing on examples that range from Internet retailer Zappos to the comedy troupe Upright Citizens Brigade to a daring gang of jewel thieves, Coyle offers specific strategies that trigger learning, spark collaboration, build trust, and drive positive change. Coyle unearths helpful stories of failure that illustrate what not to do, troubleshoots common pitfalls, and shares advice about reforming a toxic culture. Combining leading-edge science, on-the-ground insights from world-class leaders, and practical ideas for action, The Culture Code offers a roadmap for creating an environment where innovation flourishes, problems get solved, and expectations are exceeded.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\">Culture is not something you are&mdash;it&rsquo;s something you do. The Culture Code puts the power in your hands. No matter the size of your group or your goal, this book can teach you the principles of cultural chemistry that transform individuals into teams that can accomplish amazing things together.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;\">Advance praise for The Culture Code</p></div></div></div><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; overflow-y: hidden;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: -600px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; display: block !important; line-height: 25px;\"><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px;\"><br></div></div></div></div>', '2024-06-13 22:28:03', '2024-06-13 22:28:03');
INSERT INTO `Books` VALUES (10, 'Atomic Habits: An Easy & Proven Way To Build Good Habits & Break Bad Ones', 13, 3, 1, 7, 7, 2020, NULL, 456888, 999, 0, 340, 'Bìa cứng', '14.5 x 20.5', '1718292674094-608996235.jpg', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\" id=\"isPasted\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Atomic Habits: An Easy &amp; Proven Way To Build Good Habits &amp; Break Bad Ones</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">THE PHENOMENAL INTERNATIONAL BESTSELLER - 1 MILLION COPIES SOLD</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Transform your life with tiny changes in behaviour, starting now.</strong></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; font-size: 1em; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: nunito-sans, sans-serif, Helvetica, Arial; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\">People think that when you want to change your life, you need to think big. But world-renowned habits expert James Clear has discovered another way. He knows that real change comes from the compound effect of hundreds of small decisions: doing two push-ups a day, waking up five minutes early, or holding a single short phone call</p>', '2024-06-13 22:31:39', '2024-06-13 22:31:39');
